* From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|macacre|macacre, macecle|slaughterhouse, butchery}}, from {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{m|la|mazacrium||massacre, slaughter, killing”, also “the head of a newly killed stag}}, from {{etyl|gml|en}} {{m|gml|*matskelen||to massacre}} (compare {{cog|de|metzeln||massacre}}), frequentive of {{m|gml|matsken|matsken, matzgen|to cut, hew}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*maitaną||to cut}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*mei-||small}}. Akin to {{cog|goh|meizan||to cut}} among others.

